-- Oil Declines on Rising U.S. Crude Inventories as OPEC Production Increase
-- Richard Stubbe
-- 2010-07-29T13:30:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/oil-declines-on-rising-u-s-crude-inventories-as-opec-production-increase.html

          
          
             Oil futures advanced in New York
after opening lower. Crude for September delivery rose 22 cents,
or 0.3 percent, to $77.21 a barrel at 9:28 a.m. on the New York
Mercantile Exchange.  
          
          


  


        